Assuming that you use the provided UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter and didn&#39;t do any overrides to this, and that the user is already logged in to your system; you can access the username as follows:

    @GetMapping(value = &quot;/login&quot;)
    public String loginGet (Authentication auth) {
        String username = auth.getName();
        return &quot;login&quot;;
    }

Spring will automatically inject the default Authentication token which is `UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken` here.

