&gt;Cannot find default setter in class org.springframework.boot.maven.Include

The error message gives you the hint what is wrong.

The `include` element should contain `groupId` and `artifactId` instead of `**/*Test.java` (are you putting something wrong here?) according to [spring boot maven plugin document][1], so the pom should look like
```xml
        &lt;plugin&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;2.6.4&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;configuration&gt;
                &lt;skip&gt;true&lt;/skip&gt;
                &lt;includes&gt;
					&lt;include&gt;
						&lt;groupId&gt;some-groupId&lt;/groupId&gt;
						&lt;artifactId&gt;some-artifactId&lt;/artifactId&gt;
					&lt;/include&gt;
                &lt;/includes&gt;
            &lt;/configuration&gt;
        &lt;/plugin&gt;
```
  [1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/maven-plugin/reference/htmlsingle/#goals-repackage-parameters-details-includes

