The problem in your code is that you try to return a `double` for `circle` in `Area()` but you have declared `Area()` to return an `int` in your abstract class. 

There are two possible ways to fix this:
#### Round `double` value for `Area()` of `circle()` to `int`
You can do this similar to the following. This will make sure that the rounded value will actually fit into an `int`. 
```java
int longCastToInt;
try {
